title: EU ‘hit list’ would reportedly impose tougher rules on big tech companies
text: European regulators are reportedly preparing a "hit list" of up to 20 big tech companies that could be subject to strict new rules.

title: EU planning tougher regulation for 'hit list' of big tech firms: FT
text: European Union regulators are making a 'hit list' of up to 20 large internet companies, potentially including Facebook , Apple , Amazon and Alphabet's Google, that will be facing new and tougher rules aimed at curbing their market power, the Financial Times reported https://on.ft.com/34NZ3lW.

title: Where Will Facebook Be in 5 Years?
text: Look for Facebook to engage its user base in new ways in the coming years.
